@nakul02 @bertholdreinwald @asurve @frreiss @aloknsingh  @dusenberrymw  There are three options for this PR, please suggest your preference:
1. Current approach: Build .so/.dll/.dylib into the jar. Pros - This simplifies deployment. Cons: We are packaging system-dependent files into our jar.
2. Similar to our approach with JCuda: Depend on separate jar: I had created systemml-accelerator package for this option, but other committers didn't like it. 
3. Ask users to build .so files from source: This complicates deployment.

